tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Wait time,
review: I underwent dental treatment with Dr. Seema Kushwaha from September to November 2017. I had a cavity filled to begin with. She performed root canal on one of molars as well extraction of a wisdom tooth. I had a very good experience with my treatment. The root canal treatment was practically painless and so was the tooth extraction. The best part was that she is a highly proficient dental surgeon and procedures are quick. The patient feels comfortable. She is soft spoken and understands patients' concerns. She is also  honest in her assessment  and  diagnosis. My two teeth were giving me trouble for the  last two year. Now I am feeling comfortable. I will recommend to my fiends and relatives and will see her in future too, if need arises.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I am from Lagos, Nigeria and visited Dr Seema in September 2018 at the insistence of my husband after a "senior dental consultant" in a "big hospital" in Delhi in July 2017 did a very poor shoddy root canal on me which left my teeth infected, and I had to pay exorbitantly for it!

After examination, she explained to me what had been done to me previously and what needed to be done to rectify the issue. She did what she could under the circumstances and time frame I had to stay in India and we rescheduled. I returned to her in September 2019 and she carried out a minor surgery and I have immense relief, I am satisfied so far with the  result of the treatment I received.

Thank you Dr Seema.

tags: Treatment satisfaction,
context: Dental Implant Fixing,Crowns and Bridges Fixing,
review:
I went to dr Seema with some reference , about implant placement for my mother n father.
She explained nicely all the treatment options available.and what best would suit them in the long run n cost effectively too.
She has got two types of implant systems at place and put the implants  surgically in the clinic and then gave crowns on them.
The teeth and the implants are running fine n match their faces  ..
It's quite satisfying to see them smile happily after so many tooth extraction..
Highly recommend dr Seema.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I got my two front teeth fractured. I was very conscious of my smile, was really afraid to go to dentist as i feel i may need to get tooth removed or procedure will be painful as we usually hear from other people. But when i consulted dr.seema, she first helped me to overcome my fear and patiently explained about the entire procedure. I was surprised thay she said i don't require any tooth removal and entire procedure will be painless. She was very friendly and supportive throughout my treatment. She gave me porcelain veneers which enhanced my smile and covered the small gaps as well which were present in my front teeth. I m thankful to her from my heart for giving me my smile back and too beautiful one. 
I highly recommend her for any kind of dental treatment. :)

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: Dr Kushwaha has an exquisite pair of skilful hands and a reassuring smile that put me at ease the day I met her for my dental treatment. She explains the nature of the problem and offers the treatment options. Once you go for the option, she takes charge with hardly any pain or inconvenience. She is caring and always mindful of the patient's unease or physical condition. She addresses the fear element of the patient by ******* handling of her tools to extract the tooth or drill it for root canal. She is also very caring and is assisted by equally caring and competent assistants. Finally, she is reasonable with the way she charges the patient.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
The sanitisation was done properly and all the physical distancing measures were taken. I didn’t have to wait for longer. All the doctors and assistants were friendly and extremely sweet.
For my dental check-up, Dr. Seema suggested to massage my gums and do gargles instead of advising to get any kind of treatment done, which is usually the case at other dental clinic I’ve visited before.

tags: Explanation of the health issue,Doctor friendliness,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
My father is diabetic and heart patient and was wearing denture but wasn't able to have food. Our heart doctor recommended dr.seema. she explained us everything thoroughly. My father got implants done last year and now crowns. He is so happy that he can chew food properly and smile. We highly recommend dr.seema. Visit her once with your dental issue, she will give you genuine advice *** ****** **********
Thank you Dr.

reply_text: Thank you :). I m happy to give you smile you wanted.
